: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 700;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">List of Civil Engineering Lab Test:</span></p><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 700;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">Tests on Brick</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span></p><br><ul style=\"padding-inline-start: 48px;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre;\"=\"\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 700;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">Water absorption test:</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">&nbsp;This test is used to determine how much water a brick absorbs. If it absorbs less than 20%, then it is of good quality. This test is conducted by wetting the brick in water for a day and calculating the ratio between the brick\'s dry weight and saturated weight.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre;\"=\"\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 700;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">Shape and size test:</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">&nbsp;This test is based on visuals. In it, the size and shape of the test are being tested. A brick should have sharp edges. Bricks with uneven shapes can alter the required width of the wall.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre;\"=\"\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 700;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">Soundness test:</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">&nbsp;A good quality brick gives a metallic sound when smacked with another brick. This is what was determined using the soundness test.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre;\"=\"\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 700;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">Compression test:</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">&nbsp;This test determines the compressive strength of the brick. The crushing strength of the brick should be more than 3.5 N/Sqmm.</span></p></li></ul><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 700;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">Test on Fine Aggregate</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span></p><ul style=\"padding-inline-start: 48px;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre;\"=\"\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 700;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">Bulkage of sand test:</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">&nbsp;With the help of this test, we can check the volumetric change in the sand when it is saturated.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-=\"\" variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre;\"=\"\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 700;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">The density of sand:</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">&nbsp;In it, we determine the density of sand per cubic meter.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre;\"=\"\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 700;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">Silt content test:</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">&nbsp;This test is used to determine the silt and several other marine impurities in sand. The presence of these impurities can affect the strength of concrete.</span></p></li></ul><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 700;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">Tests on Cement</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span></p><ul style=\"padding-inline-start: 48px;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre;\"=\"\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 700;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">Cement consistency test:</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">&nbsp;This test is all about determining the minimum water requirement for cement. The consistency of the cement refers to the amount of water required to start a chemical reaction between cement and water.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre;\"=\"\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 700;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">Fineness test:</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">&nbsp;It is all about the particle size of cement.&nbsp;It is determined using the ratio between coarse particles to the fineness particles.</span></p></li></ul><ul style=\"padding-inline-start: 48px;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre;\"=\"\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 700;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">Compressive strength test:</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">&nbsp;The compressive strength of the cement is determined after 28 days of setting.</span></p></li></ul><div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><font color=\"#0e101a\" face=\"Century Gothic, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br></span></font></div><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 700;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">Tests on Coarse Aggregate</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span></p><ul style=\"padding-inline-start: 48px;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre;\"=\"\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 700;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">Impact value test:</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">&nbsp;It is the measure of the aggregate resistance because of a sudden shock on it.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre;\"=\"\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 700;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">Abrasion test:</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">&nbsp;It is used to determine the toughness of the aggregate material.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre;\"=\"\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 700;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">Crushing value test:</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">&nbsp;Aggregate crushing value is the resisting capability of aggregate under gradually applied compression load. The aggregate crushing value test is used to determine the relative resistance of a material.</span></p></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 700;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\"><br></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 700;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">Tests on Soil</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span></p><ul style=\"padding-inline-start: 48px;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(14,=\"\" 16,=\"\" 26);=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre;\"=\"\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" century=\"\" gothic\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" transparent;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 700;=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">Plastic limit test:</span></p></li></ul></span>', '348685Civil Engineering.png', 1, 1, 2, NULL, '2025-01-18 05:56:55', '2025-01-18 05:56:55', NULL);
INSERT INTO `blogs` (`id`, `name`, `slug`, `meta_title`, `meta_tag`, `meta_description`, `description`, `image`, `status`, `created_by`, `updated_by`, `deleted_by`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `deleted_at`) VALUES
(27, 'Primary Chemistry Lab Equipment for Colleges', 'primary-chemistry-lab-equipment-for-colleges', 'Primary Chemistry Lab Equipment for Colleges and Manufacturers', NULL, 'Chemistry Lab Equipment for colleges are useful for conducting different experiments with that Chemistry Lab Equipment manufacturers play a vital role in providing', '<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-24f3bbe5-7fff-724e-ddb7-b911396f07a2\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">\"Study of transformation can also be referred to as Chemistry.\"</span></p><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Chemistry lab equipment manufacture is fast developing in today\'s society. Rising awareness of health issues, a growing need for practical education, an increase in the number of lifestyle disorders, and the rise of health, education, and increasing Chemistry lab requirements for colleges and research businesses are driving the market for Chemistry lab equipment manufacturers.</span></p><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">We explore chemicals in chemistry labs to see how they interact under various conditions. All reactions can take occur because of the chemistry lab tools. To better grasp the world of chemistry, we need high-quality tools. What is the essential chemistry lab equipment list for college? This is what we\'ll go over in-depth in this blog. But first, let\'s go through the fundamentals.</span></p><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">What is Chemistry?</span></p><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Chemistry is the science of examining matter\'s structure, characteristics, and behavior to see what happens when they change in chemical reactions.&nbsp;</span></p><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Chemistry is the major of science that studies matter, its properties, and states. It describes how atoms interact to form elements and how elements combine to form compounds and molecules. It also defines how a substance\'s behavior changes based on the situation.</span></p><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Why do we need Chemistry?</span></p><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">We deal with chemistry daily. Chemical processes occur while you breathe, eat, walk, run, or even sleep. Chemistry is used in various fields, including atmospheric science, medicine, environmental science, agriculture science, chemical engineering, solid-state physics, biochemistry, and more.</span></p><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The following are a few applications of chemistry:</span></p><br><ul style=\"padding-inline-start: 48px;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Fuels:</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;Refining activities are likewise based on chemical principles and culminating in the production of fuels such as compressed natural gas (CNG), hydrogen, diesel, gasoline, and liquefied petroleum gas (LPG) (LPG). In this scenario, petrochemistry, a discipline of chemistry dedicated to the study of petrochemical processes, is critical. Not only are these fuels utilized in transportation, but they are also used for a range of other purposes.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Space travel:</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;Have you ever been curious about the mechanics of space travel? It\'s a dangerous situation made safer by the use of chemistry. For example, it is developing sustainable and effective fuel and unique food storage methods and inventing mechanics capable of transporting ships at large distances. Chemistry has played and will keep on playing a vital role in getting space flight to where it is currently.</span></p></li></ul><br><ul style=\"padding-inline-start: 48px;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Medicine:&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The pharmaceutical industry is strongly reliant on chemistry knowledge. Chemicals are required for the production of pharmaceuticals. Chemotherapy is used to treat several deadly diseases. Disinfectants, sterilizers, and other items all contain chemicals. If chemistry didn\'t exist, there would be no drugs.</span></p></li></ul><br><ul style=\"padding-inline-start: 48px;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Environment conservation:</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;When it comes to environmental preservation, chemistry once again plays a crucial role. All of the pollutants and greenhouse gases generated during the industrial process contribute to global warming and, ultimately, climate change. The problem now is that while these byproducts cannot be eliminated entirely, they can be minimized and processed before being discharged into the environment.</span></p></li></ul><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">We all recognize the importance of chemistry, which is why chemistry lab requirements for colleges should always be taken into account because all chemical breakthroughs, no matter how great, begins with a simple lab experiment.</span></p><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Since the beginning, <a href=\"https://aticolabexport.com/category/chemistry-lab-equipment\" title=\"Chemistry Lab Equipment Manufacturer\" target=\"\">chemistry lab equipment manufacturers</a> have worked tirelessly to develop and deliver equipment that satisfies the ever-increasing demands of chemical studies in universities. Before we get started, let\'s have a look at the chemistry lab equipment list for colleges.</span></p><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Fundamental Chemistry Lab Tools:&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">                                              <img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/BAYJMd5.png\" width=\"300\"><br></span></p><br><ol style=\"padding-inline-start: 48px;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p 