(38, 'Physics Laboratory Equipment Complete List for High School', 'physics-laboratory-equipment-complete-list-for-high-school', 'Physics Laboratory Equipment Complete List for High School', 'physics lab equipment list, physics lab equipment for Shool', 'Get complete physics lab equipment list and uses guide from India\'s leading manufacturer In India. All Physics instruments required for high school.', '<b style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-26bf3120-7fff-c3fd-96b8-9c9202a280b1\"><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">A Complete Physics Lab Equipment List for High Schools</span><span style=\"font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></h2><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Physics has its soul in observation, analysis, exploration, and more. It is more than a subject course. It is about developing skills and systemic ways of knowing the unknown and exploring more about what is known. All of it requires a huge range of physics laboratory equipment.&nbsp;</span></p><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Schools setting physics labs must ensure students\' proper understanding of physics to equip labs with </span><a href=\"https://www.aticoexport.com/physics-lab-equipment-list-and-their-uses/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#1155cc;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:underline;-webkit-text-decoration-skip:none;text-decoration-skip-ink:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">A-Z of physics lab equipment</span></a><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">.&nbsp;</span></p><br><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">36 Physics Lab Equipment List for High School, College</span></h2><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Get each of these physics lab equipment for the value they bring in enhancing physics learning and understanding to young minds:&nbsp;</span></p><br><ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;Ammeter</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: Students learn to measure electric current. In the physics lab, it is vital equipment as it teaches students how to measure a small amount of current. To properly understand electrical circuits, an ammeter helps students learn about current flow and circuit behavior concepts</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Battery Eliminator</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: This equipment teaches students how a battery eliminator is an excellent alternative when you have dead or damaged batteries. Battery eliminators teach students how to turn on the required device by understanding a stable DC power source, replacing batteries, and the need for a consistent voltage supply in experiments.</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Beaker</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: In the Physics lab is for mixing, volume measurement, and the preparation of solutions - however it also serves an educational function by providing students with foundational skills necessary for both Chemistry and Physics studies. </span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Bunsen Burner</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: Students explore the concept of heat transfer, combustion, and temperature regulation with Bunsen Burner. Students must learn how to operate a Bunsen burner with caution to learn how to heat, sterilize, and gain practical experience in controlled heating techniques for various experiments.</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Compass</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: Learning about magnets and their magnetic properties is an interesting physics concept. Magnetic compass teaches students about the interaction between a compass and magnetic fields. They learn about the properties of magnets, Earth\'s magnetic field, and navigation principles.</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Copper Calorimeter</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: It teaches students how to measure the heat transfer, specific heat capacities, and energy changes during chemical reactions.</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Daniel Cell</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: It is a wonderful piece of equipment to teach students how it converts chemical energy into electrical energy. It aims to provide a consistent voltage source for laboratory experiments and educational purposes in electrochemistry and electricity.</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Density Ball</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: Students utilizing Density Balls gain important physics concepts such as buoyancy and density through studying object\'s behavior in fluids; it helps them comprehend the effects of temperature on density liquids.</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Galvanometer</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: It is another vital equipment for students learning about electrical currents. It teaches students to measure the intensity and direction of small electrical currents. They get a good understanding of the basics of circuitry and current detection.</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Glass Slab:</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"> Glass slabs of various sizes are common in physics lab equipment. These slabs teach students the principles of refraction, reflection, and dispersion of light. The slabs are transparent and rectangular with flat parallel surfaces. Students who pass light through the glass slab understand how light changes direction and color in different mediums.</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Magnet</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: With various magnets, students play and learn about the properties of magnets, magnetic fields, and magnetic materials.</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Meter Bridge with Pencil Jockey</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"> teaches students the relationships between resistance, voltage, and current. It tells about how these principles help for accurate measurements in electrical circuits.</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Microscope</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: Enabling students to magnify and observe tiny objects under magnification. Children especially can use microscopes to explore the microscopic world.</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Mirror</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: Optical experiments are a part of many physical lab experiments. Mirrors teach students about reflection, image formation, and the properties of plane mirrors.</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Ohm\'s Law Apparatus</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: The Ohm\'s Law Apparatus in physics laboratories investigate and validate Ohm\'s Law. It is used in physics laboratories to understand the relationship between resistance, voltage, and current in an electrical circuit.</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Optic Bench</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: It helps in the alignment and setting of optical elements like mirrors, lenses prisms and lenses as well as teaching students the applications of optics in everyday life.</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Optical Table</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: Students perform complex optics experiments with optics tables in physics laboratories for precision optical experiments. It is excellent for creating a highly stable and vibration-free environment for setting up and aligning optical components. </span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Parallelogram Apparatus</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: apparatus introduces students to vector concepts, vector addition, and resultant vector quantities.</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Pendulum</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: support to understand effective means of studying concepts like periodic motion, gravitational forces and simple harmonic motion.</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Potentiometer</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: with this students measure potential difference (voltage) and control electrical circuits, as well as learn calibration and application of potential dividers in physics lab experiments.</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Prisms</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: Prisms are transparent optical equipment with smooth surfaces that refract, reflect, and disperse light to help explain optics concepts to students.</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Resistor</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: It is self-explanatory equipment. It is an equipment where students grasp the function of resistors in circuits. The equipment teaches them about current-voltage relationships and how to calculate resistance values.</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Resonance Apparatus</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: Its primary purpose is to teach the concept of resonance. It helps students learn resonance, frequency matching, and energy transfer in mechanical systems.</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Screw Gauge</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: When students get comfortable using rulers and vernier calipers, teach them to use screw gauges. It precisely measures the dimensions of small objects, components, or gaps more than any other measuring equipment. </span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Sonometer</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: Sound is an important physics equipment that needs equipment like a sonometer to conduct sound experiments. Students understand and explore wave characteristics, frequency, and wavelength relationships with a sonometer.</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Spectrometer</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: used in physics optics lab equipment help students to measure and analyze the characteristics of light, including its wavelengths, intensity, and distribution. This analysis provides insights into various physical phenomena. </span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Spectral Analysis</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: Spectrophotometers use this technique to analyze and break down complex waveforms. Then, their components, or frequencies, are studied. </span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Spring Scale</span><span style=\"font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">: A spring scale is a mechanical device. It provides the quantitative measurement of weight. It utilizes the deformation of a spring when a force is applied. </span><span